1
00:02:00,560 --> 00:02:03,720
Honestly, I don't trust anyone
in this family.

2
00:02:03,800 --> 00:02:05,960
It's obvious they're all
just after the inheritance.

3
00:02:06,040 --> 00:02:07,680
Why should I give up the inheritance?

4
00:02:07,760 --> 00:02:10,039
He believes he's the grandson,

5
00:02:10,120 --> 00:02:11,320
but he's not.

6
00:02:11,400 --> 00:02:13,000
<i>I feel so guilty.</i>

7
00:02:13,080 --> 00:02:14,840
I shouldn't have sent you there.

8
00:02:16,960 --> 00:02:18,040
<i>Something's happened to Miss Rajit?</i>

9
00:02:18,120 --> 00:02:20,400
It would be for the best
if something did happen to them.

10
00:02:20,480 --> 00:02:23,360
You are the one closest to the suspect.

11
00:02:23,440 --> 00:02:26,040
If you won't help me,
how am I supposed to continue?

12
00:02:32,040 --> 00:02:34,000
Miss Rajit.

13
00:02:38,560 --> 00:02:39,960
Miss Rajit was attacked?

14
00:02:40,800 --> 00:02:41,640
That's right.

15
00:02:42,680 --> 00:02:46,400
I didn't see the face, but it's definitely
someone from Som Song Saeng House.

16
00:02:48,160 --> 00:02:51,600
Her trip to the plantation
wasn't planned in advance.

17
00:02:52,320 --> 00:02:53,400
There's no way it was an outsider.

18
00:02:54,480 --> 00:02:55,960
What do you need me to do?

19
00:02:57,160 --> 00:02:58,600
I'm going to hand out
supplies to the workers.

20
00:02:59,240 --> 00:03:03,360
That's when you send the police in
to search the workers' quarters.

21
00:03:04,880 --> 00:03:07,120
The culprit must have left
some evidence behind.

22
00:03:09,240 --> 00:03:11,400
But Mr. Thatri, don't forget,

23
00:03:11,480 --> 00:03:13,200
this isn't your real family.

24
00:03:14,000 --> 00:03:15,960
You don't have to go to such lengths.

25
00:03:22,840 --> 00:03:23,680
I know.

26
00:03:24,200 --> 00:03:26,000
But as long as I'm living under this roof,

27
00:03:29,120 --> 00:03:31,680
I must do my best
to protect everyone in it.

28
00:03:45,320 --> 00:03:46,200
<i>Here are some eggs.</i>

29
00:03:46,280 --> 00:03:47,440
Thank you, madam.

30
00:03:49,920 --> 00:03:51,160
Share these with everyone.

31
00:04:00,480 --> 00:04:01,720
Here are some eggs.

32
00:04:01,800 --> 00:04:03,280
Thank you.

33
00:04:07,800 --> 00:04:08,960
What are you all doing?

34
00:04:09,040 --> 00:04:11,760
RIght? Why are there
so many workers gathered here?

35
00:04:11,840 --> 00:04:13,720
What's happening?

36
00:04:14,320 --> 00:04:16,120
Mr. Thatri is giving us some supplies.

37
00:04:21,720 --> 00:04:23,240
- Thank you.
- Wow.

38
00:04:23,320 --> 00:04:27,000
Giving them supplies
like this during wartime?

39
00:04:27,080 --> 00:04:28,520
What a waste.

40
00:04:29,360 --> 00:04:30,880
Where is your common sense?

41
00:04:31,960 --> 00:04:32,880
But I suppose

42
00:04:32,960 --> 00:04:35,960
when you get things for free,
you don't really know the value of money.

43
00:04:37,640 --> 00:04:40,680
Oh, come on, Pae.
Everyone is struggling right now.

44
00:04:40,760 --> 00:04:43,080
A little help won't hurt.

45
00:04:43,160 --> 00:04:44,320
Whatever.

46
00:04:52,040 --> 00:04:53,520
- Search this place.
- Yes, sir.

47
00:05:24,240 --> 00:05:25,680
- Got anything?
- Nothing yet, sir.

48
00:05:25,760 --> 00:05:27,160
- Keep looking.
- Yes, sir.

49
00:05:33,000 --> 00:05:34,040
Search everything.

50
00:06:00,560 --> 00:06:01,600
District Officer,

51
00:06:03,480 --> 00:06:04,480
I've found something.

52
00:06:07,800 --> 00:06:08,880
Which room was this found in?

53
00:06:09,400 --> 00:06:10,880
The room at the far end, sir.

54
00:06:18,360 --> 00:06:19,840
We've found the evidence.

55
00:06:24,480 --> 00:06:25,400
Evidence?

56
00:06:28,440 --> 00:06:30,120
Why is the house crawling with police?

57
00:06:31,200 --> 00:06:33,640
It might be about
the person who attacked Rajit.

58
00:06:33,720 --> 00:06:34,560
Where did you find it?

59
00:06:34,640 --> 00:06:36,280
In the very last room.

60
00:06:41,840 --> 00:06:43,280
Who does that room belong to?

61
00:06:43,360 --> 00:06:44,400
Wai, sir.

62
00:06:46,760 --> 00:06:47,800
Wai…

63
00:06:47,880 --> 00:06:49,760
- Where is he?
- Right here.

64
00:06:51,160 --> 00:06:52,200
He was just here.

65
00:06:53,080 --> 00:06:54,440
Find him.

66
00:07:06,680 --> 00:07:07,920
There you are, Wai.

67
00:07:12,720 --> 00:07:14,120
Where have you been?

68
00:07:16,080 --> 00:07:18,000
Miss Rajit has gone missing

69
00:07:18,080 --> 00:07:19,640
while riding a horse to the plantation.

70
00:07:23,600 --> 00:07:25,000
Do you want me to look for her?

71
00:07:25,520 --> 00:07:27,480
You don't seem surprised at all.

72
00:07:29,720 --> 00:07:31,440
If you suspect me, just say it.

73
00:07:35,440 --> 00:07:38,000
I only hope that my suspicions are wrong.

74
00:07:38,720 --> 00:07:41,840
Why did you do this, Wai?

75
00:07:41,920 --> 00:07:44,960
Oh, Wai. Why?

76
00:07:46,160 --> 00:07:47,880
Why?

77
00:07:47,960 --> 00:07:50,440
Maybe there's been some mistake.

78
00:07:51,200 --> 00:07:52,040
‪Hey, you.

79
00:07:52,760 --> 00:07:53,680
Mistake?

80
00:07:53,760 --> 00:07:56,520
The police found the evidence.

81
00:07:57,040 --> 00:08:00,600
He's lived here without gratitude,
only to turn and hurt his own household.

82
00:08:01,240 --> 00:08:03,440
Let the police
drag him off to rot in jail.

83
00:08:04,920 --> 00:08:08,680
Pae, Bang-orn is already
heartbroken enough.

84
00:08:08,760 --> 00:08:10,880
Have some sympathy for a mother's pain.

85
00:08:11,600 --> 00:08:13,520
That's exactly why
she should've known better.

86
00:08:14,280 --> 00:08:15,960
How on earth did you raise him?

87
00:08:16,040 --> 00:08:17,960
You let your own son
turn into such a monster.

88
00:08:35,960 --> 00:08:36,799
‪Hey!

89
00:08:40,240 --> 00:08:41,440
Wai.

90
00:08:42,360 --> 00:08:43,679
Just turn yourself in to the police.

91
00:08:43,760 --> 00:08:45,240
Your sentence might be lightened.

92
00:08:56,640 --> 00:08:58,760
Mr. Thatri, are you hurt?

93
00:08:58,840 --> 00:09:00,960
I'm fine. Keep moving.

94
00:09:18,960 --> 00:09:19,800
Don't bother running.

95
00:09:19,880 --> 00:09:21,520
You aren't getting away with this.

96
00:10:43,760 --> 00:10:44,720
About time you woke up.

97
00:10:48,560 --> 00:10:50,320
You monster!

98
00:10:50,400 --> 00:10:52,360
Why did you do it?

99
00:10:52,440 --> 00:10:54,880
Tell me why! Give me an answer!

100
00:10:54,960 --> 00:10:56,520
- Why?
- Auntie Orn.

101
00:10:56,600 --> 00:10:59,040
- Tell me why!
- Auntie, calm down.

102
00:10:59,120 --> 00:11:00,520
Please, try to breathe.

103
00:11:01,040 --> 00:11:04,560
Didn't I tell you not to cause trouble?
You ungrateful child!

104
00:11:04,640 --> 00:11:06,040
You have no sense of gratitude

105
00:11:06,120 --> 00:11:08,440
for the roof over your head. You're just…

106
00:11:08,520 --> 00:11:09,480
Auntie Orn…

107
00:11:10,320 --> 00:11:13,000
Why did you do it? Answer your mother.

108
00:11:13,080 --> 00:11:15,720
- Why did you attack Miss Rajit?
- Auntie, take it easy.

109
00:11:20,600 --> 00:11:22,240
Because she deserved it!

110
00:11:47,960 --> 00:11:49,000
- Help!
- Rajit!

111
00:11:49,520 --> 00:11:53,760
Uncle Ree! Help!

112
00:12:03,600 --> 00:12:05,560
Why would you do this to me?

113
00:12:06,320 --> 00:12:08,320
I've never done anything to you.

114
00:12:11,320 --> 00:12:13,040
This wasn't your first attempt, was it?

115
00:12:14,880 --> 00:12:16,800
What do you mean?

116
00:12:17,720 --> 00:12:18,960
It's not his first attempt?

117
00:12:19,800 --> 00:12:21,800
Ever since Colonel Nakamura
searched this house.

118
00:12:22,320 --> 00:12:23,640
It's impossible

119
00:12:23,720 --> 00:12:27,560
that he would have targeted us
unless someone blabbed to him.

120
00:12:41,720 --> 00:12:42,680
Uncle Ree?

121
00:12:52,760 --> 00:12:54,960
Was it really you, Wai?

122
00:12:55,040 --> 00:12:56,280
That's right.

123
00:12:56,880 --> 00:12:58,680
I told Colonel Nakamura myself

124
00:12:59,200 --> 00:13:02,520
that there was an American soldier
hiding in Som Song Saeng House.

125
00:13:02,600 --> 00:13:03,840
So what?

126
00:13:04,800 --> 00:13:06,480
Even if Rajit were arrested or killed,

127
00:13:06,560 --> 00:13:08,240
I don't see how you would benefit from it.

128
00:13:09,320 --> 00:13:11,080
Unless you're working for someone else.

129
00:13:11,160 --> 00:13:12,600
Don't you dare look down on me!

130
00:13:12,680 --> 00:13:14,960
I don't take orders from anyone.

131
00:13:15,520 --> 00:13:16,560
I did this all on my own.

132
00:13:18,120 --> 00:13:19,400
Then we're back to the start.

133
00:13:22,880 --> 00:13:24,560
Why did you do it?

134
00:13:25,480 --> 00:13:26,640
Exactly.

135
00:13:27,400 --> 00:13:28,880
We have no connection to each other.

136
00:13:28,960 --> 00:13:30,040
Why wouldn't it?

137
00:13:30,120 --> 00:13:32,440
I have a deeper connection to Mr. Som
than any of you.

138
00:13:34,160 --> 00:13:36,960
Because I'm Mr. Som's son!

139
00:13:37,840 --> 00:13:38,880
Oh, Wai.

140
00:13:41,040 --> 00:13:42,080
‪Wai.

141
00:13:42,160 --> 00:13:44,880
- Is this true, Bang-orn?
- Leave my mother out of this.

142
00:13:45,400 --> 00:13:48,760
She might have been a mistress,
but I'm still Mr. Som's son.

143
00:13:51,280 --> 00:13:53,240
If that's the truth,

144
00:13:54,120 --> 00:13:56,080
I'm willing to share the inheritance.

145
00:13:56,160 --> 00:13:58,040
I have no desire
to take advantage of anyone.

146
00:14:02,680 --> 00:14:03,880
There's no need for that.

147
00:14:05,000 --> 00:14:06,680
It's my fault.

148
00:14:08,360 --> 00:14:10,720
I allowed him to live with that delusion.

149
00:14:19,800 --> 00:14:20,880
I…

150
00:14:22,400 --> 00:14:24,640
I was Mr. Som's secret wife,

151
00:14:25,480 --> 00:14:26,760
but Wai

152
00:14:27,400 --> 00:14:29,840
is not his biological son.

153
00:14:31,560 --> 00:14:32,440
Mom?

154
00:14:35,040 --> 00:14:36,440
What really happened?

155
00:14:38,080 --> 00:14:40,520
Mr. Som was infertile.
He couldn't have children.

156
00:14:42,680 --> 00:14:44,000
That's a lie.

157
00:14:46,520 --> 00:14:48,520
You were the one who admitted it to me.

158
00:14:50,760 --> 00:14:52,960
I let you believe that

159
00:14:54,000 --> 00:14:57,480
because I didn't want you
searching for your real father.

160
00:14:57,560 --> 00:14:59,360
I feared that knowing the truth

161
00:14:59,880 --> 00:15:03,000
would take away your happiness forever.

162
00:15:06,760 --> 00:15:08,880
<i>You were just a few months old back then.</i>

163
00:15:08,960 --> 00:15:11,920
<i>Your father killed someone</i>
<i>and went on the run.</i>

164
00:15:15,960 --> 00:15:17,960
Is that her?

165
00:15:24,240 --> 00:15:27,280
Can I buy one can of powdered milk?

166
00:15:27,920 --> 00:15:31,000
I don't sell to a murderer's wife.
Get out of here.

167
00:15:31,600 --> 00:15:33,960
Right, your presence alone
is a curse on this place.

168
00:15:34,040 --> 00:15:35,280
Out with you, now.

169
00:15:35,880 --> 00:15:39,680
It's your husband the police
are hunting for, isn't it?

170
00:15:39,760 --> 00:15:42,040
- Get out!
- Oh, my baby.

171
00:15:42,120 --> 00:15:44,440
- Get out.
- Sister…

172
00:15:44,520 --> 00:15:46,080
- Leave at once.
- Get out.

173
00:15:54,880 --> 00:15:57,800
You know who I am, don't you?

174
00:15:59,680 --> 00:16:00,560
Yes, sir.

175
00:16:01,080 --> 00:16:04,120
You're the wealthiest man in Phuket.
Everyone knows you.

176
00:16:05,680 --> 00:16:07,200
If life is this hard for you here,

177
00:16:07,280 --> 00:16:09,280
why not come work at my house?

178
00:16:11,720 --> 00:16:13,760
But my husband's a murderer.

179
00:16:15,040 --> 00:16:17,360
Are the crimes his or yours?

180
00:16:25,680 --> 00:16:27,000
Come and stay at my home.

181
00:16:29,320 --> 00:16:31,400
<i>If it hadn't been for Mr. Som,</i>

182
00:16:32,560 --> 00:16:36,480
<i>both you and I would've starved</i>
<i>to death on the streets.</i>

183
00:16:40,880 --> 00:16:41,840
Yes, sir.

184
00:16:42,400 --> 00:16:44,080
Thank you so much.

185
00:16:53,320 --> 00:16:55,000
My father was a murderer?

186
00:16:57,760 --> 00:17:01,160
This is why I kept the truth from you.

187
00:17:01,240 --> 00:17:04,240
I knew it would break your heart
if you found out.

188
00:17:10,800 --> 00:17:12,000
Wai,

189
00:17:13,400 --> 00:17:14,520
it's okay.

190
00:17:15,240 --> 00:17:18,920
Truth aside, what Wai did was illegal.

191
00:17:22,359 --> 00:17:24,200
I must proceed with legal action.

192
00:17:25,319 --> 00:17:26,480
But…

193
00:17:42,320 --> 00:17:44,680
Why must you press charges
against Wai, Uncle Ree?

194
00:17:46,360 --> 00:17:48,240
I'm the one who was attacked,

195
00:17:48,320 --> 00:17:50,480
and I've already forgiven him.

196
00:17:50,560 --> 00:17:52,440
A crime is a crime.

197
00:17:52,520 --> 00:17:56,360
Do you have to end up dead
before you decide he deserves punishment?

198
00:17:58,040 --> 00:18:00,040
But Wai is truly sorry now.

199
00:18:00,680 --> 00:18:02,680
Please, Uncle Ree,
drop the charges for my sake.

200
00:18:05,480 --> 00:18:07,480
I'm doing this
because I'm worried about you.

201
00:18:08,840 --> 00:18:11,040
What if he gets comfortable
and attacks you again?

202
00:18:21,720 --> 00:18:24,080
That's all for today.
You may all head back now.

203
00:18:32,320 --> 00:18:33,680
District Officer.

204
00:18:36,520 --> 00:18:38,160
Yes, Miss Rajit?

205
00:18:40,040 --> 00:18:41,040
Well…

206
00:18:41,920 --> 00:18:43,320
About Wai,

207
00:18:44,480 --> 00:18:46,320
I don't want to press charges.

208
00:18:46,840 --> 00:18:51,000
I'd rather not turn
a small matter into a big ordeal.

209
00:18:53,000 --> 00:18:54,120
Mr. Thatri already informed me.

210
00:18:54,200 --> 00:18:55,800
It was all just a misunderstanding.

211
00:18:59,400 --> 00:19:00,400
He did?

212
00:19:01,080 --> 00:19:03,640
Yes. Now, if you'll excuse me.

213
00:19:04,240 --> 00:19:05,120
Yes, sir.

214
00:19:14,080 --> 00:19:15,640
Oh, Uncle Ree.

215
00:19:25,480 --> 00:19:26,760
If you weren't pressing charges,

216
00:19:26,840 --> 00:19:29,240
why did you tell me you would?

217
00:19:29,320 --> 00:19:31,560
You were clearly just teasing me.

218
00:19:35,560 --> 00:19:37,560
Because you're far too kind.

219
00:19:37,640 --> 00:19:39,320
I had to teach you a lesson

220
00:19:39,400 --> 00:19:42,200
that sometimes, your own kindness
can be turned against you.

221
00:19:53,000 --> 00:19:56,800
Auntie Orn, Wai, where are you going?

222
00:19:58,040 --> 00:20:00,680
Though you and Mr. Thatri
have forgiven us,

223
00:20:00,760 --> 00:20:04,080
we can no longer
stay here with any dignity.

224
00:20:10,280 --> 00:20:13,320
Don't say that. It's alright.

225
00:20:13,400 --> 00:20:15,200
You've been a hard worker,

226
00:20:15,280 --> 00:20:18,720
and Wai has always helped me,
just as Grandfather asked.

227
00:20:18,800 --> 00:20:20,960
Let's just put this all behind us.

228
00:20:23,720 --> 00:20:26,520
Thank you truly, but we must go.

229
00:20:27,120 --> 00:20:28,720
You two might have forgiven me,

230
00:20:28,800 --> 00:20:31,080
but I'm sure everyone else
in this house hasn't.

231
00:20:39,520 --> 00:20:41,000
In that case, safe travels.

232
00:20:41,080 --> 00:20:43,480
If you're in trouble,
don't hesitate to reach out.

233
00:20:54,280 --> 00:20:55,320
It's not much,

234
00:20:55,400 --> 00:20:56,840
but keep it with you.

235
00:21:07,200 --> 00:21:08,160
Take it.

236
00:21:23,760 --> 00:21:24,960
Thank you.

237
00:21:26,000 --> 00:21:28,920
You and Miss Rajit are truly good people.

238
00:21:30,120 --> 00:21:32,280
Please, be careful of those in this house.

239
00:21:35,040 --> 00:21:36,240
The wealth of this house

240
00:21:37,280 --> 00:21:38,400
carries a heavy curse.

241
00:21:40,920 --> 00:21:42,560
A curse?

242
00:21:44,600 --> 00:21:46,480
Go and read Mr. Som's diary.

243
00:21:46,560 --> 00:21:48,400
Then you'll understand everything.

244
00:21:50,240 --> 00:21:51,920
I must take my leave now.

245
00:22:44,680 --> 00:22:45,560
What are you doing?

246
00:22:52,360 --> 00:22:54,600
I'm looking for Uncle Som's diary.

247
00:23:12,800 --> 00:23:16,000
Mr. Som's personal belongings
is stored here.

248
00:23:16,080 --> 00:23:17,800
I haven't touched a single thing.

249
00:23:19,240 --> 00:23:21,120
- Thank you.
- No need.

250
00:23:21,640 --> 00:23:24,240
As his kin, these belong to you anyway.

251
00:23:25,440 --> 00:23:26,480
I'll be going now.

252
00:24:10,560 --> 00:24:13,080
<i>My days are numbered,</i>

253
00:24:14,440 --> 00:24:16,080
<i>but the guilt in my heart</i>

254
00:24:16,880 --> 00:24:18,640
<i>never fades.</i>

255
00:24:19,200 --> 00:24:21,600
<i>The sin of stealing</i>
<i>my siblings' inheritance</i>

256
00:24:22,120 --> 00:24:24,480
<i>still haunts me.</i>

257
00:24:25,280 --> 00:24:28,040
<i>Especially what I did to Suang,</i>

258
00:24:28,120 --> 00:24:30,200
<i>my youngest sister.</i>

259
00:24:30,280 --> 00:24:31,720
<i>Calling her an illegitimate child</i>

260
00:24:33,000 --> 00:24:36,240
<i>until she was forced</i>
<i>into a life of misery.</i>

261
00:24:37,520 --> 00:24:39,400
<i>I can only hope</i>

262
00:24:39,480 --> 00:24:41,840
<i>that Thatri, her son,</i>

263
00:24:42,560 --> 00:24:44,520
<i>can one day forgive his uncle.</i>

264
00:24:47,160 --> 00:24:49,040
Let me see that.

265
00:25:00,680 --> 00:25:01,840
I just remembered.

266
00:25:01,920 --> 00:25:04,320
I forgot I have a hair appointment.

267
00:25:04,400 --> 00:25:06,040
I have to go now.

268
00:25:08,680 --> 00:25:10,040
What's the rush, Paetai?

269
00:25:10,960 --> 00:25:11,840
Huh?

270
00:25:16,120 --> 00:25:16,920
Hey.

271
00:25:17,000 --> 00:25:20,960
So you just made it all up,
didn't you, Paetai?

272
00:25:21,040 --> 00:25:23,760
All those lies about Suang
being an illegitimate child.

273
00:25:25,200 --> 00:25:28,640
It's a good thing I didn't listen to you.

274
00:25:28,720 --> 00:25:31,720
I almost ended up
hurting a good man like Thatri.

275
00:25:33,640 --> 00:25:35,040
Shifting all the blame onto me, huh?

276
00:25:37,040 --> 00:25:40,160
If I hear one more remark about my mother,

277
00:25:40,240 --> 00:25:41,880
I'm taking it to court.

278
00:25:46,800 --> 00:25:50,240
If you want to pick a fight over this,

279
00:25:50,320 --> 00:25:53,040
make sure you have enough money ready.

280
00:26:01,280 --> 00:26:02,120
BANGKOK NOI HOSPITAL

281
00:26:02,200 --> 00:26:05,600
<i>I've handled the rumors about your mother.</i>

282
00:26:05,680 --> 00:26:08,320
<i>You won't have to worry</i>
<i>about that anymore when you get back.</i>

283
00:26:08,920 --> 00:26:10,960
<i>Get well soon, and come to Phuket already.</i>

284
00:26:14,520 --> 00:26:17,160
Your friend is truly remarkable.

285
00:26:17,240 --> 00:26:21,000
I told you, he's something else.

286
00:26:24,160 --> 00:26:25,840
Because of your friend,

287
00:26:25,920 --> 00:26:28,560
my name has finally been cleared.

288
00:26:29,880 --> 00:26:31,040
Exactly, Mom.

289
00:26:32,280 --> 00:26:34,160
I can't wait to see him again.

290
00:26:37,000 --> 00:26:38,480
I want to meet him too.

291
00:26:38,560 --> 00:26:41,320
I owe him so much gratitude.

292
00:26:42,240 --> 00:26:43,240
Thank you.

293
00:27:12,440 --> 00:27:13,440
Come in.

294
00:27:22,720 --> 00:27:24,880
Is your workload
always this heavy, Uncle Ree?

295
00:27:24,960 --> 00:27:27,600
And here I thought my schedule was packed.

296
00:27:33,120 --> 00:27:36,360
That's why I asked
if you'd consider selling off some.

297
00:27:39,120 --> 00:27:41,080
Are you trying to start another argument?

298
00:27:41,680 --> 00:27:43,800
I'm not. I'm just being realistic.

299
00:27:43,880 --> 00:27:45,640
With this much work,

300
00:27:45,720 --> 00:27:47,360
I'm worried you'll burn yourself out.

301
00:27:47,880 --> 00:27:50,680
Not to mention those relatives
who are only after the inheritance.

302
00:27:51,840 --> 00:27:55,280
Uncle Ree, people who are greedy

303
00:27:55,360 --> 00:27:56,720
will stay greedy regardless.

304
00:27:56,800 --> 00:27:59,960
But the companies
and the land are in our names.

305
00:28:00,040 --> 00:28:02,080
No one can take them from us.

306
00:28:02,160 --> 00:28:07,280
Everything I do
is to preserve my grandfather's legacy.

307
00:28:24,880 --> 00:28:26,080
You're doing great.

308
00:28:28,880 --> 00:28:29,760
Was that…

309
00:28:30,840 --> 00:28:32,720
a real compliment or a sarcasm?

310
00:28:34,520 --> 00:28:35,440
It's a compliment.

311
00:28:36,760 --> 00:28:39,080
I've seen how determined you are
to prove yourself.

312
00:28:40,600 --> 00:28:42,600
I won't mention
selling the fortune ever again.

313
00:29:03,040 --> 00:29:05,240
I'll be in Uncle Som's office
to finish some work.

314
00:29:05,960 --> 00:29:07,280
Of course, Uncle Ree.

315
00:29:13,840 --> 00:29:16,680
My, my! Look at those smiles.

316
00:29:16,760 --> 00:29:20,080
I thought you said you hated his guts.

317
00:29:20,160 --> 00:29:21,880
That's not true at all.

318
00:29:22,920 --> 00:29:23,800
Good to know.

319
00:29:24,400 --> 00:29:27,320
Because I'm officially
calling dibs on your Uncle Ree.

320
00:29:27,400 --> 00:29:29,120
Wake up, girl.

321
00:29:29,200 --> 00:29:30,640
Stop daydreaming.

322
00:29:30,720 --> 00:29:32,120
Who says I'm dreaming?

323
00:29:32,200 --> 00:29:34,160
I'm going to make this dream a reality.

324
00:29:35,280 --> 00:29:36,560
Uncle Ree is mine.

325
00:29:36,640 --> 00:29:37,960
He's mine.

326
00:29:38,040 --> 00:29:38,920
- He's mine.
- He's mine.

327
00:29:39,000 --> 00:29:40,320
That's enough, both of you.

328
00:29:42,280 --> 00:29:44,440
- Take a look behind you.
- What is it?

329
00:30:01,480 --> 00:30:02,560
Kajorn?

330
00:30:19,720 --> 00:30:22,040
White flowers, to say I'm sorry.

331
00:30:26,040 --> 00:30:27,880
I know they can't make up

332
00:30:27,960 --> 00:30:30,720
for the terrible things I've done to you,

333
00:30:32,080 --> 00:30:34,120
but I'm here to beg for one more chance.

334
00:30:40,400 --> 00:30:42,440
Are you really not going to forgive me?

335
00:30:43,040 --> 00:30:44,880
Just get straight to the point, Kajorn.

336
00:30:45,600 --> 00:30:48,640
What happened, and how did you get here?

337
00:30:49,240 --> 00:30:52,760
I never told you
where Som Song Saeng House was located.

338
00:30:52,840 --> 00:30:55,320
It's not that hard to find a place

339
00:30:55,400 --> 00:30:57,640
when you're following your heart.

340
00:30:59,920 --> 00:31:02,000
I told you to be honest.

341
00:31:02,080 --> 00:31:05,040
Is this all you came here to say?

342
00:31:08,320 --> 00:31:10,280
I got your address
from the school in Penang.

343
00:31:10,360 --> 00:31:12,200
The one where you attended.

344
00:31:14,000 --> 00:31:15,920
To go through all that effort,

345
00:31:17,440 --> 00:31:19,320
something bad must have happened to you.

346
00:31:20,720 --> 00:31:22,320
Don't say that, Rajit.

347
00:31:22,400 --> 00:31:24,280
I've only just realized…

348
00:31:32,520 --> 00:31:35,320
who my heart really belongs to.

349
00:31:45,280 --> 00:31:46,760
I've broken up with Suda.

350
00:31:47,440 --> 00:31:48,840
I wanted you to know

351
00:31:49,520 --> 00:31:51,040
how sincere I am.

352
00:32:13,400 --> 00:32:15,800
Mr. Thatri, sir.

353
00:32:18,160 --> 00:32:21,040
Mr. Thatri, I heard from the workers.

354
00:32:21,120 --> 00:32:23,520
Is it true Miss Rajit's
ex-lover is here to win her back?

355
00:32:23,600 --> 00:32:24,720
News travels fast.

356
00:32:25,320 --> 00:32:27,840
Interested in switching
from law to intelligence?

357
00:32:27,920 --> 00:32:29,360
I'm being serious.

358
00:32:29,440 --> 00:32:32,920
You are her uncle.
Aren't you worried about her at all?

359
00:32:33,560 --> 00:32:35,680
Worried? About what?

360
00:32:35,760 --> 00:32:39,160
Her ex is back to win her over.
She might actually be happy about it.

361
00:32:39,240 --> 00:32:42,280
- But that man--
- You seem very concerned about her,

362
00:32:43,720 --> 00:32:45,800
considering you aren't even a relative.

363
00:32:48,440 --> 00:32:51,040
- Poor Rajit, she shouldn't have.
- If it were me…

364
00:32:51,120 --> 00:32:52,320
I agree.

365
00:32:53,360 --> 00:32:54,400
How are we doing, girls?

366
00:32:55,880 --> 00:32:58,400
Where are we going to celebrate?
I'll have to get ready.

367
00:33:00,880 --> 00:33:02,360
Celebrate what, Uncle Ree?

368
00:33:02,440 --> 00:33:03,480
Well,

369
00:33:03,560 --> 00:33:06,120
Rajit getting back together
with her ex, of course.

370
00:33:06,200 --> 00:33:08,280
He traveled all the way to Phuket.

371
00:33:08,360 --> 00:33:10,320
I'd be totally swayed
by that kind of effort.

372
00:33:11,360 --> 00:33:12,760
Well, we aren't swayed.

373
00:33:12,840 --> 00:33:15,680
A man like that
is definitely up to no good.

374
00:33:17,120 --> 00:33:18,320
Aren't you being a bit harsh?

375
00:33:18,400 --> 00:33:21,520
He's a good-looking man.
He can't be that bad.

376
00:33:23,480 --> 00:33:25,760
That's because you weren't there.

377
00:33:25,840 --> 00:33:27,960
If you'd seen it,
you wouldn't be saying this.

378
00:33:28,760 --> 00:33:30,960
The wicked woman and the vile man,

379
00:33:31,040 --> 00:33:32,480
they're rotten to the core.

380
00:33:33,680 --> 00:33:35,320
Wicked and vile, you say?

381
00:33:35,400 --> 00:33:37,040
What actually went down?

382
00:33:43,200 --> 00:33:46,320
Who you choose to date or break up with

383
00:33:46,400 --> 00:33:48,200
has nothing to do with me.

384
00:33:48,280 --> 00:33:49,760
But they do.

385
00:33:49,840 --> 00:33:51,840
Because you're everything to me.

386
00:33:51,920 --> 00:33:53,440
I don't want to make the same mistakes.

387
00:33:53,520 --> 00:33:56,600
Even if you can't forgive me,
I'll accept it.

388
00:33:57,120 --> 00:33:58,880
But please know

389
00:33:58,960 --> 00:34:01,120
that my heart
has only ever belonged to you.

390
00:34:01,200 --> 00:34:03,120
Since the day we broke up,

391
00:34:03,640 --> 00:34:06,240
I've spent every moment missing you

392
00:34:06,320 --> 00:34:09,000
and drowning in my own guilt.

393
00:34:09,080 --> 00:34:11,679
- Kajorn…
- Trust me.

394
00:34:11,760 --> 00:34:13,000
- Let me go.
- Rajit.

395
00:34:13,080 --> 00:34:14,440
I said let go.

396
00:34:16,120 --> 00:34:18,440
Listen, Rajit.

397
00:34:19,000 --> 00:34:21,320
- Just give me one more chance.
- Kajorn.

398
00:34:21,400 --> 00:34:23,520
- Let me go. I said let go.
- Rajit.

399
00:34:23,600 --> 00:34:25,239
- Please.
- Let me go right now.

400
00:34:25,320 --> 00:34:27,199
Good heavens, Rajit.

401
00:34:27,280 --> 00:34:30,000
Are you actually
bringing men into this house now?

402
00:34:33,360 --> 00:34:35,159
Kajorn is an old friend of mine.

403
00:34:35,239 --> 00:34:38,199
He just stopped by to visit
and is leaving shortly.

404
00:34:38,280 --> 00:34:40,639
Choose your words more carefully, Auntie.

405
00:34:41,880 --> 00:34:44,120
Are you actually sending me away?

406
00:34:44,199 --> 00:34:47,600
I'm a stranger in this city.
Just let me stay the night.

407
00:34:48,560 --> 00:34:51,920
Oh, please. I think my words are correct.

408
00:34:52,800 --> 00:34:55,199
I don't mean to judge,

409
00:34:55,760 --> 00:34:57,160
since we're all adults here,

410
00:34:57,240 --> 00:34:59,840
but you should at least
show some pity for Uncle Som.

411
00:34:59,920 --> 00:35:01,840
He won't be able to rest in peace

412
00:35:01,920 --> 00:35:05,240
knowing his favorite granddaughter

413
00:35:05,320 --> 00:35:08,560
is opening the doors
for a man to stay the night.

414
00:35:16,360 --> 00:35:18,560
He's so vile, he cheated
with his girlfriend's own friend.

415
00:35:19,320 --> 00:35:21,720
Even letting him set foot
in this house is an insult.

416
00:35:21,800 --> 00:35:23,480
You're absolutely right.

417
00:35:23,560 --> 00:35:24,800
I'm still so angry for her.

418
00:35:24,880 --> 00:35:27,800
Rajit was far too kind to let that man in.

419
00:35:27,880 --> 00:35:31,440
He's such a manipulator,
playing the sorry card.

420
00:35:31,520 --> 00:35:33,680
Rajit was just
too awkward to kick him out.

421
00:35:34,400 --> 00:35:37,160
Should we do it ourselves?

422
00:35:37,240 --> 00:35:39,600
We could report him for trespassing.

423
00:35:39,680 --> 00:35:41,720
- In a case like this--
- She let him in herself.

424
00:35:42,760 --> 00:35:44,640
You'll be charged
with filing a false report.

425
00:35:46,280 --> 00:35:49,200
Then what should we do, Uncle Ree?

426
00:35:50,960 --> 00:35:52,320
We stay out of it.

427
00:35:52,400 --> 00:35:55,200
When it comes to love, if outsiders meddle

428
00:35:55,280 --> 00:35:57,080
and they're back together,
you'll look like a fool.

429
00:35:57,160 --> 00:36:00,280
Oh. Rajit isn't like that.

430
00:36:03,840 --> 00:36:06,600
Other bonds can be broken if one tries,

431
00:36:07,280 --> 00:36:10,360
but the bond of longing
is hardest to sever.

432
00:36:10,960 --> 00:36:14,200
All things can be cut,
strange as it seems,

433
00:36:14,720 --> 00:36:17,440
but the cut of love never holds.

434
00:36:17,960 --> 00:36:19,360
Have you never heard that?

435
00:36:20,280 --> 00:36:23,200
I say we stay put.
Don't meddle in their affairs.

436
00:36:23,800 --> 00:36:25,040
I can't just stand by.

437
00:36:25,960 --> 00:36:29,040
We can't let Miss Rajit
be deceived all over again.

438
00:36:32,200 --> 00:36:33,040
- Huh?
- What's that?

439
00:36:36,480 --> 00:36:39,800
How dare you insult me?
You ungrateful child!

440
00:36:39,880 --> 00:36:41,320
I wasn't insulting you.

441
00:36:41,400 --> 00:36:44,120
I'm simply saying
that if I've done something wrong,

442
00:36:44,200 --> 00:36:45,840
then take it out on me alone.

443
00:36:46,440 --> 00:36:48,360
Don't bring Grandfather into this.

444
00:36:48,440 --> 00:36:50,560
After all, I'm not the only one

445
00:36:50,640 --> 00:36:52,160
who owes him everything.

446
00:36:52,240 --> 00:36:55,280
Auntie Paetai, if it weren't for him,

447
00:36:55,360 --> 00:36:58,320
you'd still be
a street vendor selling noodles.

448
00:36:59,600 --> 00:37:01,720
Argh! How dare you talk back to me?

449
00:37:03,120 --> 00:37:04,120
You little harlot!

450
00:37:04,760 --> 00:37:06,960
- Don't you dare!
- Calm down, please.

451
00:37:07,040 --> 00:37:08,520
Don't you touch my friend.

452
00:37:09,760 --> 00:37:10,640
- Wait.
- Argh!

453
00:37:11,400 --> 00:37:13,040
If you lay a finger on my friend,

454
00:37:13,120 --> 00:37:14,800
this won't end well for you.

455
00:37:16,040 --> 00:37:17,040
Miss Paetai,

456
00:37:17,560 --> 00:37:19,120
please calm down.

457
00:37:19,200 --> 00:37:21,520
If things escalate, it won't be worth it.

458
00:37:25,040 --> 00:37:27,440
I was only trying
to protect her reputation.

459
00:37:27,520 --> 00:37:29,600
Is that so wrong?

460
00:37:30,960 --> 00:37:31,880
Goodness,

461
00:37:31,960 --> 00:37:34,360
with a house full of people,

462
00:37:34,440 --> 00:37:36,360
she still invites a man to stay the night.

463
00:37:36,960 --> 00:37:40,480
I can only imagine, back in Penang,

464
00:37:40,560 --> 00:37:42,000
how scandalous she was back then.

465
00:37:48,040 --> 00:37:49,880
This is all your fault, Mr. Kajorn.

466
00:37:49,960 --> 00:37:52,440
You've brought scandal
and trouble to Miss Rajit.

467
00:37:52,960 --> 00:37:56,160
Go back to wherever you came from.

468
00:37:56,240 --> 00:37:58,120
Rajit and I are friends.

469
00:37:58,200 --> 00:37:59,840
What's wrong with visiting a friend?

470
00:37:59,920 --> 00:38:02,240
You're all just making up stories.
And you're kicking me out?

471
00:38:02,320 --> 00:38:03,640
Are you all insane?

472
00:38:03,720 --> 00:38:05,000
He has a point.

473
00:38:05,680 --> 00:38:08,560
If we kick everyone out because
of some troubles, it would be chaos.

474
00:38:09,480 --> 00:38:12,200
How about we just kick Paetai out instead?

475
00:38:12,280 --> 00:38:13,400
Problem solved.

476
00:38:17,680 --> 00:38:19,280
You dare try to kick me out?

477
00:38:19,360 --> 00:38:21,640
I own half of this house along with Rajit.

478
00:38:21,720 --> 00:38:23,240
Why wouldn't I have the right?

479
00:38:23,320 --> 00:38:25,440
Besides, you eat and sleep here

480
00:38:25,520 --> 00:38:27,080
without contributing a single satang.

481
00:38:28,080 --> 00:38:30,200
Why should I keep you around?
It's a waste.

482
00:38:33,960 --> 00:38:35,440
I'm staying here

483
00:38:35,520 --> 00:38:38,960
to make sure no one
squanders Uncle Som's fortune.

484
00:38:39,920 --> 00:38:43,160
Don't you think I'll back down
and let you have your way.

485
00:38:57,000 --> 00:39:00,160
Look at her run the moment she loses.
She's as slippery as an eel.

486
00:39:02,760 --> 00:39:03,800
Good job, Uncle Ree.

487
00:39:07,040 --> 00:39:08,120
As for you,

488
00:39:09,560 --> 00:39:11,640
I'll have Nid drive you to a hotel.

489
00:39:11,720 --> 00:39:12,960
It's settled.

490
00:39:13,560 --> 00:39:15,240
- But I--
- Kajorn.

491
00:39:16,680 --> 00:39:20,640
Surely, you don't want to make me feel
uncomfortable like that again, do you?

492
00:39:27,760 --> 00:39:28,880
Of course.

493
00:40:28,400 --> 00:40:30,440
Are you here to thank me for today?

494
00:40:32,040 --> 00:40:34,120
Can we just call it a reward?

495
00:40:36,680 --> 00:40:38,240
I'm not Don Jose, you know.

496
00:40:48,480 --> 00:40:50,920
You already know
the whole story, don't you?

497
00:40:52,560 --> 00:40:53,560
Yeah.

498
00:40:55,040 --> 00:40:59,200
How much longer do you think
Kajorn will stay here?

499
00:41:02,760 --> 00:41:04,360
Do you want him to leave now?

500
00:41:05,560 --> 00:41:06,960
How do I do that?

501
00:41:07,040 --> 00:41:09,960
Quit your sulking
and just go back with him already.

502
00:41:11,040 --> 00:41:12,360
That's not funny.

503
00:41:12,440 --> 00:41:15,800
I'm not being funny. Why play hard to get?

504
00:41:15,880 --> 00:41:17,400
You clearly still like him.

505
00:41:18,600 --> 00:41:19,920
You're being insincere.

506
00:41:20,800 --> 00:41:22,240
How am I being insincere?

507
00:41:22,840 --> 00:41:24,960
If you don't have
a good explanation for that,

508
00:41:25,040 --> 00:41:26,920
I'm not letting this slide.

509
00:41:27,000 --> 00:41:28,840
What was it you said back in the forest?

510
00:41:30,080 --> 00:41:31,840
"I have plenty of suitors,

511
00:41:31,920 --> 00:41:33,880
but I find it all so pointless."

512
00:41:33,960 --> 00:41:36,640
"I'm an independent, educated woman."

513
00:41:37,240 --> 00:41:39,120
"Why should she care about men?"

514
00:41:41,360 --> 00:41:44,040
Don't confuse not caring with heartbroken.

515
00:41:47,720 --> 00:41:49,600
Walking away
because you can't win the argument?

516
00:41:59,520 --> 00:42:00,720
No more water for you.

517
00:42:03,480 --> 00:42:05,160
You can't take back what you give.

518
00:42:20,000 --> 00:42:21,440
What a big mouth.

519
00:42:21,520 --> 00:42:23,640
He's the most obnoxious man on earth.

520
00:42:23,720 --> 00:42:26,640
Why did someone like him
have to be my relative?

521
00:42:29,560 --> 00:42:30,400
Don Jose.

522
00:42:31,080 --> 00:42:35,400
Listen, I'll pay you with one juicy bone.

523
00:42:35,480 --> 00:42:38,960
Go bite Uncle Ree's lip for me
tonight before bed.

524
00:42:39,040 --> 00:42:40,800
Bite him hard.

525
00:42:40,880 --> 00:42:42,920
Get revenge for me, okay?

526
00:42:44,280 --> 00:42:45,120
Good boy.

527
00:42:52,800 --> 00:42:53,640
Miss Rajit.

528
00:42:56,920 --> 00:42:59,720
Vijarn, is something the matter?

529
00:43:00,440 --> 00:43:02,360
There's something I need to tell you.

530
00:43:05,200 --> 00:43:06,520
Go ahead.

531
00:43:12,800 --> 00:43:14,040
I have feelings for you.

532
00:43:19,440 --> 00:43:23,400
I've cared for you for a very long time,
but you were far too young.

533
00:43:24,000 --> 00:43:25,800
I waited until you finished your studies.

534
00:43:25,880 --> 00:43:28,520
Now that everything is in place,
I don't want to let you go.

535
00:43:28,600 --> 00:43:30,040
Please give me a chance.

536
00:43:38,920 --> 00:43:40,720
Vijarn is making a move too?

537
00:43:40,800 --> 00:43:43,040
I was just going to turn off the lights

538
00:43:43,120 --> 00:43:45,720
when I saw the lawyer
confessing his love to Miss Rajit.

539
00:43:46,920 --> 00:43:48,560
It was so romantic.

540
00:43:50,120 --> 00:43:51,120
Good grief.

541
00:43:51,200 --> 00:43:52,920
Two men at once?

542
00:43:53,680 --> 00:43:54,680
Talk about a hussy.

543
00:43:55,280 --> 00:43:57,240
You can't hide
your true colors, after all.

544
00:44:06,200 --> 00:44:08,000
You dare try to kick me out?

545
00:44:08,080 --> 00:44:10,240
I own half of this house along with Rajit.

546
00:44:10,320 --> 00:44:11,560
Why wouldn't I have the right?

547
00:44:11,640 --> 00:44:15,240
Besides, you eat and sleep here
without contributing a single satang.

548
00:44:16,240 --> 00:44:18,400
Why should I keep you around?
It's a waste.

549
00:44:26,320 --> 00:44:27,480
I've lost my appetite.

550
00:44:34,320 --> 00:44:37,320
- Let me get some rice for you, sir.
- No need. I'll handle it.

551
00:44:37,400 --> 00:44:38,440
Go back to your duties.

552
00:44:40,000 --> 00:44:41,440
One more thing.

553
00:44:43,360 --> 00:44:45,040
Remember, jobs are hard to find,

554
00:44:45,120 --> 00:44:47,080
especially during wartime.

555
00:44:48,200 --> 00:44:50,680
Think carefully before you speak.

556
00:44:50,760 --> 00:44:52,280
Do I make myself clear?

557
00:44:55,200 --> 00:44:56,520
I understand, sir.

558
00:45:08,800 --> 00:45:10,680
Is it true Miss Rajit's
ex-lover is here to win her back?

559
00:45:10,760 --> 00:45:12,600
I know this can't make up

560
00:45:12,680 --> 00:45:15,440
for the terrible things I've done to you,

561
00:45:16,800 --> 00:45:18,720
but I'm here to beg for one more chance.

562
00:45:22,560 --> 00:45:24,280
Quite the charmer, huh?

563
00:45:32,440 --> 00:45:34,120
You wanted to see me?

564
00:45:34,200 --> 00:45:35,320
How can I help you?

565
00:45:35,920 --> 00:45:37,000
I wanted to know.

566
00:45:37,080 --> 00:45:39,840
Yesterday, when you dropped
Kajorn off at the hotel,

567
00:45:39,920 --> 00:45:41,320
how did it go?

568
00:45:41,400 --> 00:45:45,080
Everything went smoothly, sir.
Just as you ordered.

569
00:45:45,160 --> 00:45:47,960
The owner there
is keeping tabs on him for us.

570
00:45:53,920 --> 00:45:56,960
And do we know when he plans
on heading back to Bangkok?

571
00:45:57,040 --> 00:45:58,960
I had the owner subtly ask.

572
00:45:59,680 --> 00:46:02,680
The guy said he's staying indefinitely.

573
00:46:09,600 --> 00:46:10,960
You can get back to work.

574
00:46:11,680 --> 00:46:12,600
Yes, sir.

575
00:46:19,160 --> 00:46:20,720
A government official

576
00:46:21,920 --> 00:46:23,920
taking such a long leave
without getting fired?

577
00:46:27,560 --> 00:46:28,640
Something doesn't add up.

578
00:46:32,200 --> 00:46:33,960
Who can I get to help me dig into this?

579
00:46:38,640 --> 00:46:40,880
<i>Sri, I need a favor.</i>

580
00:46:40,960 --> 00:46:43,520
<i>Could you look into the background</i>
<i>of Mr. Kajorn Pitakthin?</i>

581
00:46:43,600 --> 00:46:46,040
<i>He was a low-ranking</i>
<i>civil servant over in Penang.</i>

582
00:46:48,240 --> 00:46:51,240
Tri missed me! He's thinking of me!

583
00:46:51,320 --> 00:46:52,440
Oh, he's so sweet!

584
00:46:53,880 --> 00:46:56,080
What happened?!

585
00:46:56,160 --> 00:46:59,000
What's wrong? Is someone hurting you?

586
00:46:59,080 --> 00:47:01,080
What on earth are you doing?

587
00:47:02,160 --> 00:47:03,960
Have you no shame
in front of the servants?

588
00:47:05,200 --> 00:47:08,320
You're old and wrinkled.
Stop trying to show off.

589
00:47:08,400 --> 00:47:12,080
I was about to shower
when I heard your voice, so I ran over.

590
00:47:12,160 --> 00:47:14,280
So, why were you yelling?

591
00:47:20,920 --> 00:47:22,280
What are you doing?

592
00:47:23,360 --> 00:47:26,280
Tearing up a telegram from Thatri.

593
00:47:27,960 --> 00:47:30,160
He still has the nerve
to send you telegrams?

594
00:47:30,840 --> 00:47:33,880
Yes, and I've destroyed it all.

595
00:47:34,720 --> 00:47:37,160
You'll never find out where he is.

596
00:47:37,760 --> 00:47:40,120
There's no way you can stand in our way.

597
00:47:40,200 --> 00:47:41,920
But you are my wife, Srichan.

598
00:47:42,000 --> 00:47:43,600
But I love Tri.

599
00:47:44,560 --> 00:47:46,560
I only stay with you for the money.

600
00:47:47,400 --> 00:47:49,480
If you can't stand it,
then give me a payout.

601
00:47:49,560 --> 00:47:51,240
I'll go live with Tri instead.

602
00:47:52,600 --> 00:47:54,000
In your dreams.

603
00:47:54,080 --> 00:47:57,320
You'll never take my money
to go enjoy a life of luxury with him.

604
00:47:58,520 --> 00:48:00,720
And don't think for a second I don't know

605
00:48:00,800 --> 00:48:02,840
that Thatri is struggling out there,

606
00:48:02,920 --> 00:48:05,440
farming and shoveling pig manure.

607
00:48:06,440 --> 00:48:08,360
I've done my homework.

608
00:48:08,440 --> 00:48:09,960
I know he's in…

609
00:48:12,760 --> 00:48:14,000
Chiang Mai.

610
00:48:16,400 --> 00:48:19,480
You actually found out?
You know he's in Chiang Mai?

611
00:48:20,400 --> 00:48:21,480
And in this lifetime,

612
00:48:21,560 --> 00:48:25,280
I will never let you
set foot in Chiang Mai.

613
00:48:25,360 --> 00:48:27,560
Remember that, sweetheart.

614
00:48:28,320 --> 00:48:30,920
- Don't you dare touch me.
- Oh, so I can't touch you now?

615
00:48:32,280 --> 00:48:33,400
You old geezer!

616
00:48:39,240 --> 00:48:41,160
Old this, old that…

617
00:48:53,200 --> 00:48:55,360
ELIZABETH HOTEL

618
00:48:57,840 --> 00:48:59,920
His name is Kajorn Pitakthin.

619
00:49:00,920 --> 00:49:03,640
He was a low-ranking
civil servant in Penang.

620
00:49:04,360 --> 00:49:07,640
But I need more than just the basics.
Dig deep and find out everything.

621
00:49:10,240 --> 00:49:13,640
Don't you worry, madam.
I'll leave no stone unturned

622
00:49:13,720 --> 00:49:16,320
and bring you a full report
as soon as possible.

623
00:49:17,440 --> 00:49:18,840
If you'll excuse me.

624
00:49:20,320 --> 00:49:21,240
Good day.

625
00:49:57,200 --> 00:49:58,320
Seize all their supplies!

626
00:50:36,760 --> 00:50:38,080
Get on the trucks.

627
00:50:44,600 --> 00:50:45,960
Go!

628
00:50:51,400 --> 00:50:54,080
PHUKET TOWN DISTRICT OFFICE

629
00:50:56,880 --> 00:51:00,080
They're getting far too bold.

630
00:51:00,160 --> 00:51:04,200
Even a village that supplies
the Japanese army

631
00:51:04,800 --> 00:51:07,880
aren't safe from Black Beard's attacks.

632
00:51:10,000 --> 00:51:12,440
He dares to act this way
because he has powerful backing.

633
00:51:13,040 --> 00:51:14,000
It's a disgrace.

634
00:51:14,080 --> 00:51:16,560
Even now, we haven't been able to
take him down.

635
00:51:18,960 --> 00:51:20,840
Uprooting them won't be easy.

636
00:51:20,920 --> 00:51:22,440
They're becoming more violent,

637
00:51:23,120 --> 00:51:26,920
raiding cargo ships
and slaughtering villagers inland.

638
00:51:27,600 --> 00:51:29,080
We must take out Black Beard first,

639
00:51:29,760 --> 00:51:31,680
then we can go after the mastermind.

640
00:51:32,400 --> 00:51:33,840
How can we take them down?

641
00:51:34,760 --> 00:51:36,400
We don't even know where they are.

642
00:51:36,480 --> 00:51:40,200
If I knew, I would have sent my troops
to wipe them out by now.

643
00:51:46,200 --> 00:51:47,440
We may not know where they hide,

644
00:51:48,800 --> 00:51:50,600
but there are other ways
to take them down.

645
00:52:03,080 --> 00:52:04,480
- What the hell?
- That's enough!

646
00:52:04,560 --> 00:52:07,360
Stop it! Both of you!

647
00:52:07,440 --> 00:52:08,920
- Argh!
- Stop!

648
00:52:09,000 --> 00:52:10,920
- Both of you, stop!
- Bring it on.

649
00:52:11,000 --> 00:52:13,480
- That's enough.
- Both of you, please let me go.

650
00:52:14,840 --> 00:52:16,040
I need to teach him a lesson.

651
00:52:16,120 --> 00:52:18,720
Come at me, then.
You think I'll back down?

652
00:52:21,080 --> 00:52:22,400
What's going on, Auntie Jiam?

653
00:52:23,000 --> 00:52:23,880
‪Well…

654
00:52:29,080 --> 00:52:30,200
It's him.

655
00:52:31,400 --> 00:52:32,840
He's acting like a dog in the manger.

656
00:52:33,520 --> 00:52:35,120
I just wanted to invite Miss Rajit out,

657
00:52:35,200 --> 00:52:36,520
but he kept interfering

658
00:52:37,160 --> 00:52:38,760
and making sarcastic remarks.

659
00:52:38,840 --> 00:52:41,040
And what right do you have?

660
00:52:41,120 --> 00:52:43,360
Rajit and I are in love.

661
00:52:44,080 --> 00:52:45,400
Who do you think you are?

662
00:52:45,480 --> 00:52:48,280
Kajorn, please. We've broken up.

663
00:52:54,040 --> 00:52:55,520
You heard her loud and clear.

664
00:52:56,840 --> 00:52:58,640
Now, get lost.

665
00:52:58,720 --> 00:53:00,640
You're nothing but Rajit's employee.

666
00:53:00,720 --> 00:53:01,960
Know your place.

667
00:53:02,560 --> 00:53:04,240
- Come on.
- Stop it!

668
00:53:04,800 --> 00:53:06,120
Enough, both of you.

669
00:53:07,280 --> 00:53:08,480
This is not a boxing ring.

670
00:53:08,560 --> 00:53:09,600
Stop at once,

671
00:53:09,680 --> 00:53:11,440
or you're both out.

672
00:53:18,920 --> 00:53:21,200
- I'm leaving this in your hands.
- Yes, sir.

673
00:53:22,000 --> 00:53:23,680
As for the two of you,

674
00:53:23,760 --> 00:53:25,600
go your separate ways and cool off.

675
00:53:25,680 --> 00:53:27,400
I'll have someone keep an eye on you.

676
00:53:30,560 --> 00:53:32,200
Come along.

677
00:53:32,280 --> 00:53:33,400
Let's go.

678
00:53:54,560 --> 00:53:56,120
Thank you, Uncle Ree.

679
00:53:58,480 --> 00:54:00,560
It's alright, Helen.

680
00:54:03,160 --> 00:54:04,240
Helen?

681
00:54:04,320 --> 00:54:06,080
You know, Helen of Troy.

682
00:54:06,160 --> 00:54:08,320
A full-blown war just to win your heart.

683
00:54:09,000 --> 00:54:11,560
Just like you. You should be proud.

684
00:54:12,320 --> 00:54:14,000
Why are you blaming me, Uncle Ree?

685
00:54:14,080 --> 00:54:15,560
That's so unfair.

686
00:54:15,640 --> 00:54:18,800
They started fighting on their own.
I didn't do anything.

687
00:54:20,000 --> 00:54:21,800
I know you didn't instigate it.

688
00:54:22,480 --> 00:54:24,640
It was the stupidity of those two men.

689
00:54:27,280 --> 00:54:28,600
But you're a woman.

690
00:54:28,680 --> 00:54:31,440
In situations like this,
you're the one who pays the higher price.

691
00:54:33,400 --> 00:54:34,560
Am I right?

692
00:54:39,760 --> 00:54:41,960
Then what do you want me to do?

693
00:54:42,480 --> 00:54:45,560
Vijarn is our lawyer.
He handles all our affairs.

694
00:54:45,640 --> 00:54:47,880
And Kajorn hasn't actually
done anything wrong yet.

695
00:54:47,960 --> 00:54:50,960
I can't just evict him without a reason.

696
00:54:52,360 --> 00:54:53,560
Then you'll have to live with it.

697
00:54:54,160 --> 00:54:56,440
Is that really the best advice you have?

698
00:54:56,520 --> 00:54:58,760
I'll figure it out myself, then.

699
00:55:00,200 --> 00:55:03,240
Suit yourself, Helen.

700
00:55:04,600 --> 00:55:06,480
- Uncle Ree.
- Mr. Thatri.

701
00:55:07,080 --> 00:55:09,880
Sir, the District Officer
sent something for you.

702
00:55:42,960 --> 00:55:43,920
A gun?

703
00:56:21,840 --> 00:56:24,320
Uncle Ree, what are you doing?

704
00:56:24,400 --> 00:56:25,240
Hey!

705
00:56:26,760 --> 00:56:27,760
Rajit!

706
00:56:27,840 --> 00:56:28,800
<i>Don't ever do that again.</i>

707
00:56:28,880 --> 00:56:30,800
I was worried about you, okay?

708
00:56:33,400 --> 00:56:35,600
I'm not surprised
to see your here every day.

709
00:56:35,680 --> 00:56:37,000
What exactly do you want?

710
00:56:37,080 --> 00:56:39,120
All I ask for is your forgiveness, Rajit.

711
00:56:41,080 --> 00:56:42,880
According to my detective,

712
00:56:42,960 --> 00:56:45,160
Kajorn already has a wife.

713
00:56:45,240 --> 00:56:46,720
But they aren't legally married.

714
00:56:48,000 --> 00:56:50,520
<i>Is anyone home? I'm looking for Miss Suda.</i>

715
00:57:24,880 --> 00:57:26,880
Subtitle translation by:
Khathathong Thongtumlueng
